ZH: 他把时间浪费在了鞍前马后，没有什么实际的成果。
EN: He wasted time running around like a headless chicken, without any actual results.

ZH: 现在的他总是鞍前马后，整天都忙忙碌碌。
EN: He is always bustling around and being busy all day long.

ZH: 她平时都是鞍前马后，非常努力地工作。
EN: She is always busy and works very hard.

ZH: 由于他总是鞍前马后，导致了任务无法按时完成。
EN: Because he is always rushing around, the task cannot be completed on time.

ZH: 老板让他鞍前马后，希望能把项目提前完成。
EN: The boss asked him to work overtime in the hope of completing the project ahead of schedule.

ZH: 我们需要合作，不能总是鞍前马后，没有效果。
EN: We need to cooperate, instead of running around like a headless chicken, which is ineffective.

ZH: 他们鞍前马后，终于完成了这个艰巨的任务。
EN: They worked around the clock and finally completed the challenging task.

ZH: 对于他们来说，日常工作就是鞍前马后，太累了。
EN: For them, daily work is the hustle and bustle of life, which is exhausting.

ZH: 他不喜欢鞍前马后，更喜欢安静地工作。
EN: He doesn't like running around like a headless chicken and prefers to work quietly.

ZH: 这次旅行真是让我鞍前马后，累坏了。
EN: This trip really made me busy, and I'm exhausted.

ZH: 他总是在鞍前马后，真的需要好好休息一下。
EN: He is always hustling and bustling, and really needs to take a good rest.

ZH: 别老是鞍前马后，适当的休息也是很重要的。
EN: Don't always be so busy, taking breaks is also very important.

ZH: 因为经常鞍前马后，导致身体状况变差了。
EN: Because of constant rushing around, the physical condition deteriorated.

ZH: 我们需要合理安排工作和休息，不要总是鞍前马后。
EN: We need to schedule work and rest properly, instead of always being busy.

ZH: 在这个团队里，大家都是鞍前马后，为完成项目而努力。
EN: In this team, everyone is working hard to complete the project.

ZH: 经理一直让我鞍前马后，加班加点地工作。
EN: The manager always asks me to work overtime and put in extra effort.

ZH: 他这几天鞍前马后，为接下来的考试做准备。
EN: He has been busy preparing for the upcoming exam these days.

ZH: 要学会合理安排时间，不要整天鞍前马后。
EN: You need to learn to schedule your time properly, instead of rushing around all day.

ZH: 鞍前马后可能会增加工作量，但并不一定会提高效率。
EN: Running around like a headless chicken may increase workload, but may not necessarily improve efficiency.

ZH: 老板喜欢员工鞍前马后地工作，但也需要注意保护好自己的身体。
EN: The boss likes employees to work hard, but they also need to take care of their health.
